SOME BASIC DETAILS FOR TERRAFORM:-
---------------------------------------------------------------
---------------------------------------------------------------
** Terraform is an open source "Infrastructure as a code Tool" created by hashicorp 

** A declarative code tool, Terraform enables the developers to use high-level configuration
language called HCL ("Hashicorp configuration language") to describe the desired "End-State"
cloud or on-premises infrastructure for running an application

** Terraform uses a simple-syntax, can provision infrastructure across multiple clouds

IAAC:-
---------------------------------------------------------------
** Infrastructure as a code (IAAC) is the managing and provisioning of infrastructure
through code instead of through manual processes

** With IaC, configuration files are created that contain your infrastructure specifications
which makes it easier to edit and distribute configuration.

**IaC allows you to meet the growing needs of infrastructure changes in a scalable and trackable 
manner

** The insfrastructure terraform could handle low-level elements like Networking, storage
compute instances, also high-level elements like SaaS features,DNS entries etc..

** It is famous for easy to use but not true for complex environments, it is not easy.

WHY:-
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
** It is a service orchestration tool (chef, ansible and puppet are configuration tools)

** Declarative code('it can be changable')

** imputable code('we can't able to change the code once its written')

CLOUD ALTERNATIVES:-
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

** AWS --> CloudFormation Templates (JSON/YAML)

** AZURE --> ARM Templates (JSON)

** TERRAFORM --> AWS (IOL), AZURE(BP), GCP(HP), VMWARE

** FUEL --> CODE

ADVANTAGES:-
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
** Terraform is having the readable code

** Dry run

** importing of resources is easy

** Creating of multiple resources

** can create modules for repeatable code

DISADVANTAGES:-
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
____________________________________________________________________________________________

** IT IS 3RD PARTY TOOL. IT TAKES TIME TO ACCOMODATE NEW SERVICES.

